title: PML-N’s Sohaib Malik wins PP-71 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League (PML-N) candidate, Sohaib Ahmad Malik has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-71, Sargodha-I by securing 55,050 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Independent candidate, Naeem Haider who bagged 49,076 votes.
The voters’ turnout remained 53.87%.
